text: Pare (or Mojokuto) is a town in the Kediri regency (kabupaten) within the province of East Java, Indonesia. Pare is well known as the English Village (Indonesian: Kampung Inggris) which is located at Tulungrejo, West Pare. == References == * Geertz, Clifford. The Religion of Java. Free Press, 1960. University of Chicago, 1976. [Originally a PhD thesis, Harvard University, 1956.] * English Village Information Website info kampung inggris.
